==English==
[[Image:Life raft.jpg|thumb|an inflatable life raft]]
===Etymology===
Old Norse ''[[raptr]]'', originally "beam", "rafter". Cognate with "[[rafter]]".
===Pronunciation===
*(UK) [[IPA]]: /rɑːft/
*(US) [[IPA]]: /ræft/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːft|-ɑːft]]
===Noun===
'''raft''' (''plural:'' '''rafts''')
# a [[flat]] [[structure]] made of [[plank]]s, [[barrel]]s etc., that [[float]]s on [[water]], and is used for [[transport]], [[emergency|emergencies]] or a [[platform]] for [[swimmer]]s
# a flat-bottomed [[inflatable]] [[craft]] for [[float]]ing or [[drift]]ing on water
# a large (but unspecified) number, [[a lot]]
#:''All we've ever got from you is a '''raft''' of promises.''

====Related terms====
*[[life raft]]
